org.apache.flex.compiler.mxml

Interface IMXMLDataManager

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    MXMLDataManager

    public interface IMXMLDataManager
    The IMXMLDataManager of the IWorkspace maintains a cache of IMXMLData objects that serve as DOMs for MXML files.

    If an MXML file is used in multiple projects, its MXMLData can be shared. Its symbol table and parse tree cannot be shared, because the meaning of various MXML tags could be different in different projects.

    • Method Detail

      • get

        IMXMLData get(IFileSpecification fileSpec)
        Gets the IMXMLData for the specified MXML file. If the manager already has the IMXMLData for the file, it returns it. Otherwise, it will parse the MXML file, store the IMXMLData, and return it.
        Parameters:
        fileSpec - An IFileSpecification object specifying an MXML file.
        Returns:
        An IMXMLData object representing the tags, attributes, and text in the MXML file.

      • invalidate

        void invalidate(IFileSpecification fileSpec)
        Removes any cached IMXMLData objects for the specified file.
        Parameters:
        fileSpec - An IFileSpecification for the file being invalidated.
